WHAT IS THIS FILE
The certified display profile for the Sony BVM-HX3110 4K HDR Master Monitor.
It defines the dual-layer LCD technology, peak luminance specifications,
color volume, EOTF characteristics (PQ, HLG, SDR), bit depth pipeline,
interface support (12G-SDI, 25G-SDI, ST 2110), and factory calibration
parameters. This file is the single source of truth for configuring a
GIOP Output Device Transform (ODT) targeting the BVM-HX3110.

WHY IT EXISTS
The BVM-HX3110 is the reference mastering display for high-end cinema and
broadcast HDR. Every ODT that targets this monitor must know its exact
black level (true 0.0000 nit), peak luminance (4000 cd/m²), and color
volume. Without this certified profile, a grade mastered on the BVM may
look different on another display, or a trim pass may clip highlights that
the BVM could have shown. This file provides the auditable display model.

HOW IT WORKS
This file specifies:
  1. Panel technology and its implications for contrast and blooming.
  2. Peak luminance, black level, and the resulting dynamic range.
  3. Color primaries and color volume coverage (DCI-P3, Rec.2020).
  4. Internal bit depth and processing pipeline.
  5. Supported EOTFs and calibration targets.
  6. Physical interfaces and signal formats.
  7. Factory calibration procedure and expected Delta-E performance.

